      "title": "Standing Barbell Low-to-High Chest Press",
      "context": "Stand in a split stance with your core engaged to keep your torso stable. Hold the barbell with an overhand grip just below your collarbone, elbows slightly below shoulder level at about a 45-degree angle, palms facing forward, and shoulder blades naturally retracted and depressed. Exhale as you press the barbell upward along a slight diagonal to just in front of your head, elbows nearly fully extended but not locked. Inhale as you slowly and controlledly lower it back to the starting position. Throughout the movement, avoid shrugging your shoulders or overextending your lower back. This exercise primarily targets the upper chest, front deltoids, and triceps, while also demanding strong core stability.",
      "showDetails": "[{\"img\":\"https://d1rwzqjevxdih5.cloudfront.net/1748917538109.jpg\",\"context\":\"1.Engage your core to maintain torso stability.\\n2.Hold the barbell with an overhand grip just below your collarbone.\\n3.Keep your elbows slightly below shoulder level at about a 45-degree angle, palms facing forward, with your shoulder blades naturally retracted and depressed.\"},{\"img\":\"https://d1rwzqjevxdih5.cloudfront.net/1748917541123.jpg\",\"context\":\"1.Exhale as you press the barbell along a slightly upward diagonal path to the front of your head, with your elbows nearly fully extended but not locked.\"}]",
